{"name":"Breakpoints-js","tagline":"Tiny script to sync CSS Media Query Breakpoints to Javascript","body":"<!-- You need this one to define your breakpoints: -->\r\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"css/breakpoints.css\">\r\n<!-- We only need this one for this demo: -->\r\n<link href=\"http://netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/twitter-bootstrap/2.3.2/css/bootstrap-combined.no-icons.min.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\r\n    \r\n#  Breakpoints.js Demo\r\n\r\n_    Resize your browser to see these values change_\r\n\r\n* Current breakpoint is: <em id=\"currentBreakpoint\">Dunno yet</em>\r\n* Previous breakpoint was: <em id=\"previousBreakpoint\">Dunno yet</em>\r\n* These breakpoints are defined in the CSS: <em id=\"cssBreakpoints\">Dunno yet</em>\r\n* The window.breakpoints property looks like this: <em id=\"breakpointsObject\">Dunno yet</em>\r\n* These classes have been added to the &lt;html&gt; element: &quot;<em id=\"htmlClasses\">Dunno yet</em>&quot;\r\n\r\n<!-- You need these if you want to use the breakpoints object or the breakpoint event: -->\r\n<script src=\"http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.10.2/jquery.min.js\"></script>\r\n<script src=\"src/breakpoints.min.js\"></script>\r\n    \r\n<!-- We only need this for the demo in old IE: -->\r\n<!--[if lt IE 8]><script src=\"http://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/json2/20121008/json2.min.js\"></script><![endif]-->\r\n\r\n<script>\r\n\r\n      // Initialise fields when page is ready:\r\n      $(function(){\r\n\r\n        $('#cssBreakpoints'   ).text( $('HEAD *').css('fontFamily') )\r\n        $('#breakpointsObject').text( JSON.stringify(window.breakpoints) )\r\n        $('#htmlClasses'      ).text( $('HTML').attr('class') )\r\n        $('#currentBreakpoint').text( window.breakpoints.current )\r\n\r\n      })\r\n\r\n      // Update ui whenever our custom *breakpoint* event fires:\r\n      $(window).on( 'breakpoint', function( e, current, previous ){\r\n\r\n        if( window.console ){ console.log( e, current, previous ) }\r\n\r\n        $('#breakpointsObject' ).text( JSON.stringify(window.breakpoints) )\r\n        $('#htmlClasses'       ).text( $('HTML').attr('class') )\r\n        $('#currentBreakpoint' ).text( current )\r\n        $('#previousBreakpoint').text( previous )\r\n        \r\n      })\r\n\r\n</script>\r\n","google":"","note":"Don't delete this file! It's used internally to help with page regeneration."}